eventsFunctionsExtensions.author: 4ian
eventsFunctionsExtensions.name: Parallax
eventsFunctionsExtensions.shortDescription: Behaviors to animate Tiled Sprite objects in the background, following the camera with a parallax effect.
eventsFunctionsExtensions.description: Behaviors to animate Tiled Sprite objects in the background, following the camera with a parallax effect.

eventsBasedBehaviors.description: Move the image of a Tiled Sprite to follow the camera horizontally with a parallax effect. After adding this to an object, put the object on a layer that is not moving, behind the layer that is followed (for example, a layer called "Background").
eventsBasedBehaviors.fullName: Horizontal Parallax for a Tiled Sprite
eventsBasedBehaviors.name: HorizontalTiledSpriteParallax

propertyDescriptors.label: Parallax factor (speed for the parallax, usually between 0 and 1)
propertyDescriptors.name: ParallaxFactor

propertyDescriptors.label: Layer to be followed (leave empty for the base layer)
propertyDescriptors.name: FollowedLayer

eventsBasedBehaviors.description: Move the image of a Tiled Sprite to follow the camera vertically with a parallax effect. After adding this to an object, put the object on a layer that is not moving, behind the layer that is followed (for example, a layer called "Background").
eventsBasedBehaviors.fullName: Vertical Parallax for a Tiled Sprite
eventsBasedBehaviors.name: VerticalTiledSpriteParallax

propertyDescriptors.label: Parallax factor (speed for the parallax, usually between 0 and 1)
propertyDescriptors.name: ParallaxFactor

propertyDescriptors.label: Layer to be followed (leave empty for the base layer)
propertyDescriptors.name: FollowedLayer

eventsFunctionsExtensions.fullName: Mobile virtual keyboard for Text Entry
eventsFunctionsExtensions.name: TextEntryVirtualKeyboard
eventsFunctionsExtensions.shortDescription: Allow to open and close the virtual keyboard on mobile (iOS, Android). To be used with Text Entry objects.
eventsFunctionsExtensions.description:
Allow to open and close the virtual keyboard on mobile (iOS, Android). To be used with Text Entry objects.

Actions to open and close the keyboard are added. You can then use the Text Entry as usual.

eventsBasedBehaviors.description: Allow to open and close the virtual keyboard on mobile (iOS, Android). To be used on Text Entry objects.
eventsBasedBehaviors.fullName: Mobile virtual keyboard for Text Entry
eventsBasedBehaviors.name: TextEntryVirtualKeyboard

events.comment: For each object which have this behavior, we create a HTML input with a unique ID. This ID is stored in the object to allow to retrieve the input later.

eventsFunctions.name: openKeyboard
eventsFunctions.sentence: Open mobile keyboard, and save input in _PARAM0_

events.comment: When we delete the object with this behavior, we delete the HTML input linked to it

eventsFunctionsExtensions.author: @arthuro555 and @Add00
eventsFunctionsExtensions.name: InputValidation
eventsFunctionsExtensions.shortDescription: Conditions and expressions to check, sanitize and manipulate strings.
eventsFunctionsExtensions.description: Provides conditions to check if a string is a valid phone number, url, email, number, contains only letters. Also provides expressions to manipulate strings (count number of lines, remove new lines, remove non alphanumerical characters).

eventsFunctions.description: Check if the string is a valid phone number.
eventsFunctions.fullName: Check if a string is a valid phone number
eventsFunctions.name: IsValidPhoneNumber

eventsFunctions.description: Check if the string is a valid URL.
eventsFunctions.fullName: Check if a string is a valid URL
eventsFunctions.name: IsValidUrl

eventsFunctions.description: Check if the string is a valid email.
eventsFunctions.fullName: Check if a string is a valid email
eventsFunctions.name: IsValidEmail

eventsFunctions.description: Check if the string represents a number (potentially with a minus sign and potentially with a decimal point).
eventsFunctions.fullName: Check if a string represents a number
eventsFunctions.name: IsValidNumber

eventsFunctions.description: Check if the string has only latin alphabet letters.
eventsFunctions.fullName: Check if a string has only latin alphabet letters
eventsFunctions.name: IsOnlyLetters

eventsFunctions.description: Returns the string without the first line.
eventsFunctions.name: RemoveFirstLine

events.inlineCode: eventsFunctionContext.returnValue = eventsFunctionContext.getArgument("text").substring(eventsFunctionContext.getArgument("text").indexOf("\n") + 1);

parameters.description: String to remove the first line from
parameters.name: text

eventsFunctions.description: Count the number of lines in a string.
eventsFunctions.name: CountNewLines

events.inlineCode: eventsFunctionContext.returnValue = eventsFunctionContext.getArgument("text").split(/\r\n|\r|\n/).length;

parameters.description: The text to count lines from
parameters.name: text

eventsFunctions.description: Replaces every new line character with a space.
eventsFunctions.fullName: Replace new lines by a space
eventsFunctions.name: RemoveNewLines

parameters.description: The text to remove new lines from
parameters.name: text

eventsFunctions.description: Remove any non-numerical and non A-Z characters.
eventsFunctions.fullName: Remove any non-numerical and non A-Z characters
eventsFunctions.name: ToAlphanumerical

events.inlineCode: eventsFunctionContext.returnValue = eventsFunctionContext.getArgument("text").replace(/\W/g, '');
